~~البطون 79. `umar (may allah be pleased with him) said: i heard
~~messenger of allah (pbuh) saying: "if you all depend on allah with due
~~reliance, he would certainly give you provision as he gives it to birds
~~who go forth hungry in the morning and return with full belly at dusk".
~~[at-tirmidhi]. commentary: trust in allah does not mean that one should
~~not give any importance to material resources. what it really means is
~~that along with their due importance, one should have full trust in
~~allah. without his will, material resources are of no avail. but
~~nevertheless it is necessary to have material resources because their
~~procurement is also ordained by him. birds do not keep sitting in their
