~~people, went to one of the rooms of his wives. the people were startled
~~at his haste, and when he came out and saw their astonishment at his
~~urgency he said, "i recalled that there was left with me some gold which
~~was meant for charity; i did not like to keep it any longer, so i gave
~~orders that it should be distributed". [al-bukhari]. in another
~~narration, messenger of allah said, "i had left some gold for sadaqah in
~~the house, and did not wish to keep it overnight". commentary: 1. a
~~person should not keep such a thing because of which his attention is
~~diverted from allah (swt) towards that thing. 2. although it is
~~undesirable to jump over the neck of people in ordinary circumstances
~~but it is permissible when special conditions warrant it. PageV01P0110

