~~hafiz ibn hajar is of the opinion that it is equal to twelve thousand
~~human steps. (for detail please see the book `mir'atul mafatih' chapter
~~salat-us-safar). if it stands for the mileage even then it gives an idea
~~of the heat of the sun. although it is billions of miles away from the
~~earth but one cannot bear its heat in summer. when the sun shall be at a
~~distance of one mile, its heat shall be so intense that people would be
~~immersed in sweat. may allah save us from it. PageV01P0502

