~~reported: in the pre-islamic period of ignorance, i used to think that
~~people who used to worship idols, were deviated and did not adhere to
~~the true religion. then i heard of a man in makkah who was preaching a
~~message. so i mounted my camel and went to him. i found that (this man
~~who was) messenger of allah (pbuh) remained hidden because of the
~~persecution by his people. i had entered makkah stealthily and when i
~~met him i asked him, "who are you?'' he (pbuh) said, "i am a prophet.''
~~i asked; "what is a prophet?'' he said, "allah has sent me (with a
~~message)". i asked, "with what has he sent you?'' he said, "he sent me
~~to strengthen the ties of kinship, to destroy idols so that allah alone
