# allah, the exalted, says: "verily, the likeness of (this) worldly life
~~is as the water (rain) which we send down from the sky; so by it arises
~~the intermingled produce of the earth of which men and cattle eat: until
~~when the earth is clad in its adornments and is beautified, and its
~~people think that they have all the powers of disposal over it, our
~~command reaches it by night or by day and we make it like a clean-mown
~~harvest, as if it had not flourished yesterday! thus, do we explain the
~~ayat (proofs, evidences, verses, lessons, signs, revelations, laws,
~~etc.) in detail for the people who reflect.'' (10:24) "and put forward
~~to them the example of the life of this world: it is like the water
