~~earlier. in this hadith, `aishah (may allah be pleased with her) has
~~related an account of the extremely austere and pious life of the
~~prophet (pbuh) although her house was the house of his most beloved
~~wife. this hadith also tells us that in spite of his profound love for
~~`aishah (may allah be pleased with him), the prophet (pbuh) did not
~~accord her any preferential treatment. he treated all his wives equally.
~~thus, this hadith has a lesson for `ulama' and their families that they
