# وعن أنس رضي الله عنه قال : لم يأكل النبي صلى الله عليه و سلم على خوان
~~حتى مات وما أكل خبزا مرققا حتى مات . رواه البخاري وفي رواية له : ولا رأى
~~شاة سميطا بعينه قط 494. anas (may allah be pleased with him) reported:
~~the prophet (pbuh) neither ate on a dining cloth, nor ate soft bread
~~throughout his life. [al-bukhari]. one narration adds: he (pbuh) never
~~even saw a samit lamb. samit is an animal prepared for food by removing
~~its hair by boiling water, and then roasted without being skinned. this
~~type of food is preferred by wealthy people. (editor's note) commentary:
~~it means that the prophet (pbuh) has not adopted the ways of the rich
~~but embraced a simple way of life which is the mode of fuqara' - poor
~~people. thus, he remained contented with simple food and had no relish
~~for extravagant feasts. PageV01P0606

