~~attention. first, there is an account of the exemplary character of the
~~companions who became unmindful of their own needs when they saw that
~~somebody else was more needy and deserved assistance. second, there is
~~an allowance for accepting a gift provided one's heart is free from
~~desire for it. third, a man is allowed to accumulate wealth but on the
