### ||| AUT 600 -
# وعن أبي هريرة رضي الله عنه عن النبي صلى الله عليه و سلم قال : [ ما
~~بعث الله نبيا إلا رعى الغنم ] فقال أصحابه : وأنت ؟ قال : [ نعم كنت
~~أرعاها على قراريط لأهل مكة ] رواه البخاري 600. abu hurairah (may allah
~~be pleased with him) reported: messenger of allah (pbuh) said, "every
~~prophet has tended sheep''. he was asked: "and did you?'' he replied,
~~"yes, i tended them for a few carats for the makkans.'' [al-bukhari].
~~commentary: the prophet (pbuh) used to graze the sheep of makkans for a
~~few carats (a carat is one-twentieth, or a bit more, of a dinar). this
~~practice was indeed a divine training for the prophets so that it might
~~be easier for them to deal with humans and forbear afflictions which
~~came to them from men. a shepherd indeed needs greater patience and
~~forbearance to look after his herd. this practice proved useful to the
~~prophets. moreover, this hadith is suggestive of the adoption of a
~~lawful occupation, no matter how people may look askance at it. that was
~~the reason why the prophets took such occupations. PageV01P0736

