~~tormented.''' [muslim]. commentary: according to this hadith, power and
~~superiority (honour), greatness and grandeur are divine attributes
~~alone. if anybody tries to invest himself with these attributes or
~~claims them, it means that he is audacious enough to claim godhood.
~~allah says that it is the result of his sheer grace to a man if he
~~enjoys these qualities in a restricted measure, and he is supposed to be
~~obedient and grateful to him for that. in no manner does it behave him
~~to trumpet his own grandeur and greatness. if someone out-steps his
~~limits in this regard, he will get himself into hell. the hadith is a
~~signal of warning to men that they must not boast of their power and
~~behave arrogantly towards their fellow-humans. PageV01P0761

