~~716. `abdullah bin yazid al-khatmi (may allah be pleased with him)
~~reported: when messenger of allah (pbuh) intended to bid farewell to his
~~army he would say: "astau-di'ullaha dinakaum, wa amanatakum, wa
~~khawatima `amalikum (i entrust allah with your deen, your trust and your
~~last deeds).'' [abu dawud]. commentary: this hadith presents the same
~~benediction as stated above. yet, here its addresses are the plural
~~number of second person, whereas in the previous hadith it was singular
~~number. the hadith points out the virtue desirability of the leader to
~~bid farewell to his army before they set out for the battlefield, and to
~~advise them using the prophet's words stated above, reminding them to
~~hold fast to their religion for which they have left everything behind
~~to fight for it and to win allah's mercy. PageV01P0904

