~~السحولية ] بفتح السين وضمها وضم الحاء المهملتين : ثياب تنسب إلى سحول :
~~قرية باليمن و [ الكرسف ] : القطن 786. `aishah (may allah be pleased with
~~her) reported: the body of messenger of allah (pbuh) was shrouded in
~~three white yemeni cotton garments, among which was neither a gown nor a
~~turban. [al-bukhari and muslim]. commentary: the shroud of a dead body
~~consists of three simple pieces of cloth to the exclusion of a turban,
~~shirt and izar. it is better for the shroud to be white. PageV01P1001

