~~as should serve as a barrier between us and acts of disobedience; and
~~such obedience as will take us to your jannah; and such as will make
~~easy for us to bear in the calamities of this world. o allah! let us
~~enjoy our hearing, our sight and our power as long as you keep us alive
~~and make our heirs from our own offspring, and make our revenge
~~restricted to those who oppress us, and support us against those who are
~~hostile to us let no misfortune afflict our deen; let not worldly
~~affairs be our principal concern, or the ultimate limit of our
~~knowledge, and let not those rule over us who do not show mercy to
~~us).'' [at-tirmidhi]. commentary: this hadith reveals a prayer through
~~which we may be able to reach all that which is good in this world as
~~well as in the hereafter. PageV01P1063

### ||| AUT 835 -
