~~sat down. messenger of allah (pbuh) said, "thirty.'' [abu dawud and at-
~~tirmidhi]. commentary: this hadith shows that we can earn ten-fold good
~~rewards by greeting a person in the islamic way. there will be a further
~~ten-fold addition to it if we say, "as-salamu `alaikum wa rahmatullah".
~~may you be safe from evil, and the mercy of allah be upon you). and if
~~we say, "as-salamu `alaikum wa rahmatullahi wa barakatuhu'' may you be
~~safe from evil, and the mercy of allah and his blessings be upon you),
~~thirty-fold good reward comes to us. but ahadith are silent on
~~increasing more words to salam. so this much will suffice. PageV01P1087

### ||| AUT 852 -
