### ||| AUT 871 -
# وعن سهل بن سعد رضي الله عنه قال قال رسول الله صلى الله عليه و سلم : [
~~إنما جعل الاستئذان من أجل البصر ] متفق عليه 871. sahl bin sa`d (may
~~allah be pleased with him) reported: the messenger of allah (pbuh) said,
~~"seeking permission to enter (somebody's house) has been prescribed in
~~order to restrain the eyes (from looking at something we are not
~~supposed to look at).'' [al-bukhari and muslim]. commentary: within the
~~four walls of their homes, people are normally engaged in different
~~types of domestic chores, or they rest in seclusion. women
~~understandably do things at home in a relaxed manner which is scarcely
~~possible for them in the presence of a man not belonging to their
~~household. we commit an intrusion upon others' privacy and also eye the
~~hijab-observing women by entering a house without permission. both the
~~things are prohibited and must be avoided. PageV01P1117

