# وعن سهل بن عمرو . وقيل : سهل بن الربيع بن عمرو الأنصاري المعروف بابن
~~الحنظلية وهو من أهل بيعة الرضوان رضي الله عنهم قال : مر رسول الله صلى
~~الله عليه و سلم ببعير قد لحق ظهره ببطنه فقال : [ اتقوا الله في هذه
~~البهائم المعجمة فاركبوها صالحة وكلوها صالحة ] رواه أبو داود بإسناد صحيح
~~966. sahl bin `amr known as ibn al-hanzaliyyah reported: the messenger
~~of allah (pbuh) happened to pass by a camel whose belly was sticking to
~~its back (because of hunger), whereupon he said, "fear allah in respect
~~of these dumb (animals). ride them while they are fit, and slaughter
~~them and eat their meat when they are fit.'' [abu dawud]. commentary:
~~this hadith lays emphasis on taking care of animals. because if they are
~~hungry or you overload them, they will not be able to speak out their
~~suffering to you in human language. you are, therefore, supposed to take
~~care of their food and other requirements by yourself. in case you fail
~~in your duty to them, allah will take you to task. moreover, eating the
~~flesh of sick and lean animals is unhygienic and can endanger health.
~~whereas, the flesh of a healthy and robust animal gives energy and
~~strength to human body. PageV01P1246

