~~يكون كونا إذا وجد واستقر 973. `abdullah bin sarjis (may allah be pleased
~~with him) reported: whenever the messenger of allah (pbuh) proceeded on
~~a journey, he would seek refuge in allah from the hardships of the
~~journey, and against deviation after guidance, and against the
~~supplication of the oppressed, and occurrences of unpleasant events in
~~the family and property. he would say: "allahumma inni a`udhu bika min
~~wa`tha'is-safari, wa kaabatil-munqalabi, wal-hauri ba`dal-kauni, wa da
~~`watil-mazlumi, wa su'il-manzari fil-ahli wal-mal.'' [muslim].
~~commentary: the prophet (pbuh) sought divine refuge against the
~~supplication of the oppressed because allah immediately responds to it.
~~it is, therefore, imperative that if a man has wronged anybody, he
~~should recompense his wrongdoing before embarking on a journey because
~~the malediction of the wronged may invoke divine wrath exposing the
~~wrongdoer to a risky and troublesome journey. PageV01P1257

