~~night and stand in salat during the latter part. [al-bukhari and
~~muslim]. commentary: this hadith tells us about the ordinary routine of
~~the prophet (pbuh). ordinarily, he would go to sleep in the first part
~~of the night and perform tahajjud prayer in the later portion, which is
~~the best time for it. but, as already mentioned in the preceding
~~ahadith, he sometimes also performed it in the early as well as middle
~~hours of the night. PageV01P1507

