### ||| AUT 1194 -
# وعنها رضي الله عنها قالت : كان رسول الله صلى الله عليه و سلم يجتهد في
~~رمضان ما لا يجتهد في غيره وفي العشر الأواخر منه ما لا يجتهد في غيره .
~~رواه مسلم 1194. `aishah (may allah be pleased with her) reported: the
~~messenger of allah (pbuh) used to strive more in worship during ramadan
~~than he strove in any other time of the year; and he would devote
~~himself more (in the worship of allah) in the last ten nights of ramadan
~~than he strove in earlier part of the month. [muslim]. commentary: we
~~learn from this hadith that: 1. one should concentrate more on prayers
~~and worship on the last ten nights of ramadan than the first twenty
~~nights, in the same way as one should do more worship in ramadan than in
~~the other months. 2. one should keep oneself awake for prayer, worship
~~and glorification of allah in the last ten nights of ramadan so that one
~~can attain the blessings of lailat-ul-qadr. 3. one should also persuade
~~his family members to keep themselves awake for prayer and worship in
~~the last ten odd nights of ramadan so that they can also make efforts to
~~please allah. 4. i`tikaf (seclusion in the mosque for prayers) in the
~~last ten days of ramadan is also a meritorious act for its being a
~~practice of the prophet (pbuh). PageV01P1531

