# وعن عمر بن الخطاب رضي الله عنه قال قال رسول الله صلى الله عليه و سلم
~~: [ إذا أقبل الليل من ههنا وأدبر النهار من ههنا وغربت الشمس فقد أفطر
~~الصائم ] متفق عليه 1236. `umar bin al-khattab (may allah be pleased with
~~him) reported: the messenger of allah (pbuh) said: "when the night
~~approaches from this side (i.e., the east) and the day retreats from
~~that side (i.e., west) and the sun sets, then it is time for a person
~~observing saum (fasting) to break his fast.'' [al-bukhari and muslim].
~~commentary: the words "break his fast'' can be interpreted in two ways.
~~first, it is time to break the saum . second, the saum has reached its
~~end. whether one eats or not the saum is over because it comes to a
~~close with sunset. thus, the time for saum has been determined that it
~~begins with the daybreak and ends at sunset. any increase in this time
~~is exaggeration which is disliked by allah. PageV01P1583

