~~unsaddled camel which also carried his provisions (i.e., his zamilah).
~~[al-bukhari]. commentary: "zamilah'' is a mount like a horse, mule etc.,
~~on which luggage is loaded while travelling. what it means here is that
~~the prophet (pbuh) travelled for hajj on such a mount on which he kept
~~his provision for the journey also. in other words, it was his zamilah
