~~ثم جئت فقلت : يا رسول الله علمني شيئا أسأله الله تعالى قال لي : [ يا
~~عباس يا عم رسول الله سلوا الله العافية الدنيا والآخرة ] رواه الترمذي
~~وقال حديث صحيح 1488. abul-fadl al-`abbas bin `abdul-muttalib (may allah
~~be pleased with him) reported: i asked the messenger of allah (pbuh) to
~~teach me a supplication. he (pbuh) said, "beg allah for safety (from all
~~evils in this world and in the hereafter).'' i waited for some days and
~~then i went to him again and asked him: "o messenger of allah teach me
~~to supplicate something from allah.'' he said to me, "o al-`abbas, the
~~uncle of messenger of allah! beseech allah to give you safety
~~(al-a'fiyah ) in this life and in the hereafter.'' [at-tirmidhi].
~~commentary: the prayer for "al-a' fiyah'' includes peace and safety of
~~one's religion and one's welfare in this world as well as in the
