### ||| AUT 1563 -
# وعنه رضي الله عنه قال سمعت رسول الله صلى الله عليه و سلم يقول : [ من
~~قذف مملوكه بالزنا يقام عليه الحد يوم القيامة إلا أن يكون كما قال ] متفق
~~عليه 1563. abu hurairah (may allah be pleased with him) said: i heard
~~the messenger of allah (pbuh) saying, "he who accuses his slave of zina
~~will receive the punishment (hadd) of slander on the day of
~~resurrection, unless the accusation of zina was true.'' [al-bukhari and
~~muslim]. commentary: on the day of judgement, the masters of slaves and
~~slave-girls will be exposed to hadd-ul-qadfi (hadd for accusing someone
~~of adultery) for the reason that they perpetrate all kinds of
~~oppressions on their captives and their grievances are not redressed. on
~~the day of judgement, when almighty allah dispenses justice without any
~~prejudice and favour, he will also do full justice to this oppressed
~~class and those masters, who somehow escaped the punishment on this
~~account in this world. thus, this hadith has a stern warning for those
~~masters who are carried away by their might and authority and perpetrate
~~oppression on their servants and slaves. PageV01P1992

