### ||| AUT 1771 -
# وعن أبي هريرة رضي الله عنه أن رسول الله صلى الله عليه و سلم قال : [
~~اتقوا اللاعنين ] قالوا : وما اللاعنان ؟ قال : [ الذي يتخلى في طريق الناس
~~أو في ظلهم ] رواه مسلم 1771. abu hurairah (may allah be pleased with
~~him) said: the messenger of allah (pbuh) said, "avoid two habits which
~~provoke cursing.'' the companions said: "what are those things which
~~provoke cursing?'' he said, "relieving on the thoroughfares or under the
~~shades where people take shelter and rest.'' [muslim]. commentary: we
~~learn from this hadith that a muslim must avoid all such things which
~~cause inconvenience to other muslims. if one uses the places mentioned
~~in this hadith as toilet, this would not only cause inconvenience to the
~~public but may also cause an epidemic. it is also necessary to avoid
~~such things for the sake of cleanliness. some religious scholars are of
~~the opinion that this act is deemed to be a major sin, as it brings
~~people's curses upon the one who practices it. PageV01P2315

### || AUT 352 - باب النهي عن البول ونحوه في الماء الراكد
# chapter 352 prohibition of urinating into stagnant water PageV01P2316

### ||| AUT 1772 -
# عن جابر رضي الله عنه أن رسول الله صلى الله عليه و سلم نهى أن يبال في
