~~therefore, accepts only that which is pure. allah has commanded the
~~believers as he has commanded his messengers by saying: `o messengers!
~~eat of the good things, and do good deeds.' (23:51) and he said: `o you
~~who believe (in the oneness of allah - islamic monotheism)! eat of the
~~lawful things that we have provided you...''' (2:172). then he (pbuh)
~~made a mention of the person who travels for a long period of time, his
~~hair are dishevelled and covered with dust. he lifts his hand towards
~~the sky and thus makes the supplication: `my rubb! my rubb!' but his
~~food is unlawful, his drink is unlawful, his clothes are unlawful and
~~his nourishment is unlawful, how can, then his supplication be
~~accepted?'' [muslim]. commentary: for the grant of prayer, honest
~~earning is essential. allah accepts charity only if it has been earned
~~in an honest way. moreover, before any pious action, honest earning for
~~living is essential; otherwise good actions will also go waste.
